THE National
Police Commissioner General Khehla Sithole and Minister of Police Fikile
Mbalula have come out to condemn the killings of the five police officers in
Eastern Cape.An unknown
group of armed suspects entered the Ngcobo Police Station, between Umtata and
Queenstown in the Eastern Cape.Without
warning, the armed gunmen randomly opened fire on the officers that were on
